{
  "design_notes": "World-space 2D + altitude Z (2.5D): ships/slugs have z; visuals use fake depth (lift + scale); ballistics collide only if XY close and Z within band. delivery=ballistic = straight slug until map edge or impact (no homing). hitscan = instant beam VFX. missile = guided. Full 3D (Panda3D etc.) would be a separate renderer; same data can feed it later. Future: fleet build, capture points, carrier stances.",
  "authoring": {
    "weapons_three_layers": [
      "1) projectile_types[] \u2014 Shared ammo / beam types. The \"name\" here is the global ID (e.g. \"Fighter Missile\"). Code looks up delivery, damage, speed, range, missile turn rate, etc. Add a new row here only when you need new ballistics or a new missile profile.",
      "2) ship_classes[].weapons[] \u2014 Default guns for that hull. Each object is one firing slot at runtime. Required keys: \"name\" (any label shown in UI / debrief; flavor only), \"projectile\" (string MUST match exactly one projectile_types[].name), \"fire_rate\" (shots per second). Different ships can use the same projectile with different names and fire_rate \u2014 e.g. Fighter \"Missile Rack\" and Interceptor \"Short Missile\" both use \"Fighter Missile\"; the interceptor just fires it faster.",
      "3) ship_classes[].weapon_loadout_options[] \u2014 Optional fleet-design swaps. Each slot has \"weapon_index\" (0-based index into that class\u2019s weapons[]), \"label\" (row title in UI), and \"choices\"[]. Each choice has the same shape as a weapons[] entry plus \"scrap_cost\" (0 = default tier). weapon_index must point at an existing default weapon slot; swapping replaces that slot\u2019s RuntimeWeapon in combat."
    ],
    "add_new_gun_same_behavior": [
      "Reuse an existing projectile_types name. On the ship, add or edit a weapons[] or loadout choice: set \"projectile\" to that name and tune \"fire_rate\". Pick a distinctive \"name\" string so players see the flavor you want."
    ],
    "add_new_projectile_type": [
      "Append to projectile_types with a new unique \"name\".",
      "Use delivery \"hitscan\" | \"ballistic\" | \"missile\" and copy field patterns from a similar existing type (missiles need speed, damage, turn_rate_deg, lifetime; add \"range\" only if you want a short envelope like fighter missiles).",
      "Then reference that new \"name\" from ship weapons[] or loadout choices[].",
      "Rare special cases (e.g. PD vs asteroids, fighter missile targeting) are keyed by projectile name in demo_game.py \u2014 copy an existing branch if you add a wholly new delivery style."
    ],
    "add_loadout_row_to_capital": [
      "Ensure weapons[] already has a slot for that mount (or add one).",
      "Add weapon_loadout_options with weapon_index equal to that slot\u2019s index.",
      "First choice in each row should match the default weapons[weapon_index] stats and scrap_cost 0 so the design screen matches stock hulls."
    ],
    "ignored_keys": "You may add extra keys on weapon objects (e.g. \"note\") for your own reference; the game only reads name, projectile, fire_rate, and scrap_cost on loadout choices.",
    "weapon_modules": [
      "weapon_modules[id] defines interchangeable kit: name, projectile, fire_rate, optional mount tag.",
      "Ship weapons[] may be { module_id } or legacy inline { name, projectile, fire_rate }.",
      "weapon_loadout_options rows may use choice_set to reuse the same module list on multiple slots (e.g. battleship turret batteries).",
      "On entering fleet design, choice indices sync to current weapons so defaults match each slot."
    ]
  },
